begin\": 416, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5748044056536764, \"rank\": 0.471103612276701, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thedouble-figure medal tallyexceeded the eight in both 2008 and 1988, the best haul since the 1984 Games when now World Athletics president Seb Coe, who was watching in the stands, won gold for Great Britain.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9980530275746834, \"rank\": 0.0019507705217809066, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 742, \"end\": 749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seb Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}, {\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9987424815084361, \"rank\": 0.0012587265519348806, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's relay line-up had made two changes from the heats with Lewis Davey and Alex Haydock-Wilson coming in for Sam Reardon and Toby Harries.\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Lewis\", \"score\": 0.9916583425113281, \"rank\": 0.008411797910637323, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"score\": 0.7465829414401879, \"rank\": 0.33942337363046965, \"text\": \"Davey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999857009244, \"rank\": 1.4283532279195632e-08, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"score\": 0.9326467449626213, \"rank\": 0.0721209821497821, \"text\": \"Toby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Hudson-Smith,silver medallist in the individual event, ran a 43 flat for his, the second leg of the relay, one of the fastest ever recorded in the history of the event.\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Davey appeared to go off too quickly for the third leg but Charlie Dobson paced his 400 perfectly for a British record and a medal behind the USA and Botswana.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9999922579865614, \"rank\": 7.60760392044394e-06, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.or